OpenSMTPD extras - backends for OpenSMTPD tables

Allows using different backends for OpenSMTPD tables,
including SQLite, MySQL, PostgreSQL, LDAP.

Each backend can be activated or deactivated by setting the relevant env var to yes or no.
By default, MySQL, LDAP and SQLite backend are built, since they are pretty straightforward to use,
and everything is available on a stock slackware installation.

MYSQL=yes
LDAP=yes
SQLITE=yes
PYTHON=no
SOCKETMAP=no
POSTGRES=no   # requires potgresql
REDIS=no      # requires hiredis and redis
